      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">MU vs NU vs XI: Greek Letter Showdown</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">XI — 9 pts (Best)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X(8)+I(1). The highest-scoring 2-letter Greek word. X is the key — worth 8 points alone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">MU — 4 pts (Middle)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M(3)+U(1). Double NU's score. M is only 2 in the bag — use it wisely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">PI — 4 pts (Tied)</p>
