          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Always prefer MU over NU:</span> If you have both M and N with U, play MU (4pts) over NU (2pts). The 2-point difference compounds when you factor in premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">M on DLS = 6pts from one tile:</span> Position MU so M lands on Double Letter Score. That's 6 + 1 = 7 points from a 2-letter word — competitive with many 4-letter plays.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Plural to MUS:</span> MUS is valid — add S for 5 points total. This means MU on the board becomes a hook target for opponents though, so weigh the risk.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
